				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Too Many Mobs when Swarming..?<a name="19845"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 8 04 9:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, I don't know if that topic made much sense, but it's a problem I'm coming across.
<br />

<br />
Basically, the scenario is as follows.  I play in what is off-time for Tunare, so getting a PoP group is harder than for many americans. I've stopped doing LDoN (at least until 58 and I can start grouping with my guildmates again) because the xp is pitiful unless I'm the lowest in the group, so I'm left with LFGing for most of my night, or soloing.  
<br />
I finally stopped AE kiting non-PoP zones, and have been working on swarm kiting.  I like to think I've got it down pretty well, but I've still got a lot of 'fine tuning' to go. Anyway, PoN WW has too much down time in between swarms, (waiting on respawn) so I've been doing some big swarms in PoD, and switching between flies and rats/goos after I clean each spot out.  My problem though has been timing my invis correctly.  If I pull a lot of mobs (main fly island plus one or two more) I end up charming my pet, sic it on another, and then train remainder onto them.  The problem is that the damage can be extremely variable, and without an instant click invis, that 3 seconds for invis song to cut in costs me xp 50% of the time as a good round of attacks will pulverise my pet.  The alternative is to invis at 70%, and then risk having to chant them down 30% or more at the end.
<br />

<br />
Yes, I could just pull less mobs, but I'm trying to get more 'bang for my buck', and it seems to me that 5 second kills are the way to go.  On a purely personal note, *I* want to master this, regardless of how fast/slow xp moves.
<br />

<br />
Obviously, getting an instant click invis would be the best option, however, after a recent Stormfeather camping tour, I'm not ready to camp the courier cycle, and anything non-instant click just doesn't seem worth it. Does anyone have any tips on how to minimise my xp-less pet deaths?</span></td>
