				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Too Many Mobs when Swarming..?<a name="20383"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 10 04 7:33 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have to disagree with Daklar. 
<br />

<br />
I'm using the Goblin Gazughi Ring from the Sarnak Courier, paid 11k for it on Saryrn. It has netted me several times the plat I paid for it, definately worth it IMHO.
<br />

<br />
There's a neat feature where you can setup a key to toggle between two targets. I have this set to my ` key. After I get my swarm on my pet, I hit F1 twice to target myself and then my pet, and then I can just ` back and forth between us, and when the mob is down low enough, I ` to me, click invis, ` back to what is now my ex-pet, chant to death. Very simple, makes swarming almost trivial. 
<br />

<br />
Loouis Armsong
<br />
63 Bard</span></td>
