				<td colspan="2"><span>Aha!!  Ok, things have changed since I last played my bard a lot.  My bard is one of my first ever chars (created Dec 1999) who, for various reasons, (one of them being that I moved house to a non-cable supported area) I had to stop playing.  At that time, I could start to cast a clicky while moving, but I had to stop moving at the end of a cast or else I would get the 'spell interrupted' message.  I just assumed that when I finally got around to playing my bard again, things were still the same.  Either that, or my memory is faulty (it *was* a long time ago)
<br />

<br />
I pulled the cloak out of the bank and had a play with it, and HUZZAH! makes a huge difference - I can now clear out the main flies in PoD plus the 3 (or is it 4?) smaller islands in one hit.  Still get the occasional unlucky pet loss, but overall, things are a lot better.  Now to get some boots of the mosquito <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> 
